"body": "**Key points from solved questions**\n- Thrust is the force with which the rocket moves upward given by, $$ \\mathrm{F}=u\\frac{dm}{dt} $$ Thus mass of the gas ejected per second to supply the thrust needed to overcome the weight of the rocket is $$ \\frac{dm}{dt}=\\frac{F}{u}=\\frac{ma}{u} $$ or $$ \\begin{array}{l}\\frac{dm}{dt}=\\frac{600\\times10}{1000}\\\\ =6\\mathrm{kg}\\mathrm{s}^{-1}\\end{array} $$",
