"title": "How momentum is conserved without an external force",
"summary": "For an isolated system (no net external force), the total momentum stays constant — a direct consequence of Newton's second and third laws.",
"body": "**Must know**\n- $\\vec{F}_{ext}=0\\Rightarrow\\vec{p}_{total}=\\text{constant}$.\n- Two-body: $m_1\\vec{u}_1+m_2\\vec{u}_2=m_1\\vec{v}_1+m_2\\vec{v}_2$.\n- Recoil from rest: $m_1\\vec{v}_1+m_2\\vec{v}_2=0$ (gun and bullet move oppositely).\n**Exam traps**\n- Momentum is conserved even in inelastic collisions and explosions.\n- Internal forces cannot change the total momentum of the system.",
