"title": "How a particle stays in equilibrium under concurrent forces",
"summary": "A particle is in equilibrium when the vector sum of the forces on it is zero; resolving, ΣFx = 0 and ΣFy = 0.",
"body": "**Must know**\n- Condition: $\\sum\\vec{F}=0$, i.e. $\\sum F_x=0$ and $\\sum F_y=0$.\n- Three concurrent forces in equilibrium form a closed triangle.\n- Lami's theorem: $\\dfrac{F_1}{\\sin\\alpha}=\\dfrac{F_2}{\\sin\\beta}=\\dfrac{F_3}{\\sin\\gamma}$.\n**Exam traps**\n- Equilibrium means zero NET force, not the absence of forces.\n- Resolve along convenient perpendicular axes before summing.",
