"body": "**Must know**\n- Gravitational PE near Earth: $U=mgh$.\n- Force–PE relation: $F=-\\dfrac{dU}{dx}$.\n- A conservative force does path-independent work; its work around any closed loop is zero, $\\oint\\vec{F}\\cdot d\\vec{r}=0$.\n- Conservation of mechanical energy: $KE+PE=\\text{constant}$ when only conservative forces act.\n**Exam traps**\n- PE is defined only up to an additive constant — fix a reference level.\n- Gravity and spring forces are conservative; friction and drag are not.",
