"title": "Why a spring stores ½kx² of energy",
"summary": "A spring obeying Hooke's law (F = −kx) stores elastic potential energy U = ½kx², equal to the area under its force–extension line.",
"body": "**Must know**\n- Hooke's law (restoring force): $F=-kx$.\n- Elastic potential energy: $U=\\dfrac{1}{2}kx^2$.\n- In spring SHM the total energy $E=\\dfrac{1}{2}kA^2$ shuttles between KE and PE.\n**Exam traps**\n- $U\\propto x^2$, so it is the same for a compression $-x$ as for an extension $+x$.\n- The work done BY the spring equals $-\\Delta U$.",
