"title": "How fast a body must move to escape a planet",
"summary": "Escape speed is the minimum speed needed to leave a body's gravity with no further propulsion: vₑ = √(2GM/R) = √(2gR), about 11.2 km/s for Earth.",
"body": "**Must know**\n- $v_e=\\sqrt{\\dfrac{2GM}{R}}=\\sqrt{2gR}\\approx11.2\\ \\text{km s}^{-1}$ for Earth.\n- It is independent of the escaping body's mass and of the launch direction.\n- It is $\\sqrt{2}$ times the orbital speed at the surface: $v_e=\\sqrt{2}\\,v_o$.\n**Exam traps**\n- Escape speed does not depend on the projectile's mass.\n- Compare carefully: $v_e=\\sqrt{2}\\,v_{orbital}$.",
