"title": "How one inverse-square law explains gravity from falling apples to orbits",
"summary": "Newton's 1/r² law underlies surface gravity, potential energy, escape speed, satellite orbits and Kepler's laws — all flowing from F = GMm/r².",
"body": "**Must know**\n- Surface gravity $g=\\dfrac{GM}{R^2}$; potential energy $U=-\\dfrac{GMm}{r}$.\n- Escape speed $v_e=\\sqrt{2gR}$; orbital speed $v_o=\\sqrt{GM/r}$; orbital energy $E=-\\dfrac{GMm}{2r}$.\n- Kepler's third law $T^2\\propto a^3$.\n**Exam traps**\n- Keep escape speed ($\\sqrt{2}\\,v_o$) distinct from orbital speed.\n- The energy of a bound orbit is negative.",
