"title": "How energy shuttles between kinetic and potential in SHM",
"summary": "In SHM the total energy E = ½kA² = ½mω²A² is constant, exchanging between kinetic (½mv²) and potential (½kx²) energy.",
"body": "**Must know**\n- Kinetic energy: $KE=\\dfrac{1}{2}m\\omega^2(A^2-x^2)$; potential energy: $PE=\\dfrac{1}{2}m\\omega^2 x^2$.\n- Total energy: $E=\\dfrac{1}{2}m\\omega^2 A^2=\\dfrac{1}{2}kA^2$ (constant).\n- KE is maximum at the mean position, PE at the extremes.\n**Exam traps**\n- Total energy is proportional to the square of the amplitude.\n- The kinetic and potential energies each oscillate at twice the frequency of the motion.",
