"title": "How SHM is the projection of uniform circular motion",
"summary": "SHM is the projection of uniform circular motion onto a diameter: a reference particle moves round a circle of radius A at angular speed ω, and its shadow performs SHM.",
"body": "**Must know**\n- The projection of a particle moving uniformly on a circle of radius $A$ at angular speed $\\omega$ gives $x=A\\cos(\\omega t+\\phi)$.\n- The SHM angular frequency $\\omega$ equals the angular velocity of the reference circle.\n- The phase of the SHM is the angular position on the circle.\n**Exam traps**\n- The amplitude equals the radius of the reference circle.\n- This projection is what makes SHM sinusoidal.",
