"title": "Beats",
"summary": "<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img…",
"body": "**Key points from solved questions**\n- In case of beats formation, Unknown frequency, $$ \\mathbf{v}_{B}=\\mathbf{v}_{A}\\pm\\mathrm{b e a t s} $$ Where $$ v_{A}=530Hz,beats=6Hz $$ $$ \\begin{array}{l}\\bullet\\\\ \\bullet\\end{array} $$ $$ \\mathrm{v_{B}=530\\pm6=536,o r524H z} $$ From question, when tension of B is slightly decreased, then beats frequency increases to 7 Hz. Thus, the original frequency B is 524 Hz.\n- <div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"https://pplines-online.bj.bcebos.com/deploy/official/paddleocr/pp-ocr-vl-16-online//469c3723-cc7c-4562-abf6-545774a2e0f7/markdown_3/imgs/img_in_image_box_291_590_509_725.jpg?authorization=bce-auth-v1%2FALTAKDN8mY5KlNI7zaRpLmOqrw%2F2026-06-06T18%3A16%3A01Z%2F-1%2F%2F8c0155ea6d5694d96b41ba5a9f3cfced1cced4b4f06c5db9db4d1f924037b9e7\" alt=\"Image\" width=\"18%\" /></div> Now divide 1 second into 1, 1, 2, equal divisions $$ \\frac{1}{1},\\frac{1}{1},\\frac{2}{1} $$ By eliminating common time instants, total maxima in one second is 2.\n- Frequency of unknown source = 246 Hz or 254 Hz second harmonic of this source = 492 Hz or 508 Hz when gives 5 beats per second when sounded with a source frequency 513 Hz. Therefore, unknown frequency = 254 Hz.\n- According to the question, Frequency of the string varies directly as the square root of its tension. $$ \\begin{aligned}&\\Rightarrow\\quad f\\propto\\sqrt{\\mathrm{T}}\\\\ &\\quad\\quad\\quad\\quad\\frac{\\Delta f}{f}=\\frac{1}{2},\\frac{\\Delta\\mathrm{T}}{\\mathrm{T}}\\\\ &\\Rightarrow\\quad\\quad\\quad\\quad\\frac{\\Delta\\mathrm{T}}{\\mathrm{T}}=2,\\frac{\\Delta f}{f}\\\\ &、\\quad\\quad\\quad\\quad=2\\times\\frac{6}{600}=0.02\\\\ \\end{aligned} $$\n- We have, $$ n_{p}\\propto\\sqrt{\\mathrm{T}} $$ $$ n_{f}=frequency of tuning~fork=512Hz $$ $$ x=Beat~frequency=4~beats/s $$ Hence, $ n_{p} - n_{f} = x \\downarrow $ (wrong) $$ n_{f}-n_{p}=x\\downarrow(correct) $$ $$ n_{p}=n_{f}-x=512-4=508\\mathrm{~Hz} $$\n- According to the question, Frequency of first string, $$ \\begin{aligned}f_{1}&=\\frac{1}{2l}\\sqrt{\\frac{T}{m}}\\\\&=\\frac{1}{2\\times51.6\\times10^{-2}}\\sqrt{\\frac{20}{10^{-3}}}\\\\&=137.03Hz\\end{aligned} $$ Frequency of second string, $$ \\begin{aligned}f_{2}&=\\frac{1}{2\\times49.1\\times10^{-2}}\\sqrt{\\frac{20}{10^{-3}}}\\\\&=144.01\\mathrm{~Hz}\\end{aligned} $$ ∴ Number of beats, $$ f_{2}-f_{1}=144-137=7\\mathrm{b e a t s} $$\n- $$ Frequency=\\frac{Velocity}{Wavelength} $$ $$ \\mathrm{v}_{1}=\\frac{\\mathrm{v}}{\\lambda_{1}}=\\frac{330}{5}=66\\mathrm{~Hz} $$ and $$ \\mathrm{v}_{2}=\\frac{\\mathrm{v}}{\\lambda_{2}}=\\frac{330}{5\\cdot5}=60\\mathrm{~Hz} $$ ∴ Number of beats per second $$ \\begin{aligned}&={\\bf v}_{1}-{\\bf v}_{2}\\\\&=66-60=6.\\end{aligned} $$\n- $$ y_{1}=4\\sin500\\pi t $$ Here, $$ y_{2}=2\\sin506\\pi t $$ $$ \\omega_{1}=500\\pi,\\omega_{2}=506\\pi $$ $$ \\mathrm{v}_{1}=\\frac{\\omega_{1}}{2\\pi}=\\frac{500\\pi}{2\\pi}=250\\mathrm{Hz} $$ $$ \\mathrm{v}_{2}=\\frac{\\omega_{2}}{2\\pi}=\\frac{506\\pi}{2\\pi}=253\\mathrm{~Hz} $$ $$ \\begin{array}{l}v=v_{2}-v_{1}=253-250\\\\=3\\mathrm{beats/s}=180\\mathrm{beats/min}\\end{array} $$\n- We have, the frequency of vibrations of string, $$ n=\\frac{1}{2\\pi}\\sqrt{\\frac{g}{l}} $$ $$ \\begin{aligned}&Given,&n_{A}=2n_{B}\\\\&\\therefore&\\quad\\frac{1}{2\\pi}\\sqrt{\\frac{g}{l_{A}}}=2.\\frac{1}{2\\pi}\\sqrt{\\frac{g}{l_{B}}}\\\\&\\Rightarrow&\\quad\\frac{1}{l_{A}}=\\frac{4}{l_{B}}\\\\&\\Rightarrow&l_{B}=4l_{A}\\\\&It~is~clear~from~eq.(i),~the~frequ\\\\&string~does~not~decoord.\\end{aligned} $$\n- Beats are produced when both waves are combined. Frequency of beats will be, $$ \\mathbf{v}_{1}-\\mathbf{v}_{2}=\\frac{1}{\\mathrm{T}_{1}}-\\frac{1}{\\mathrm{T}_{2}}=\\frac{1}{3}-\\frac{1}{4}=\\frac{1}{12} $$ Hence, time period = 12 s",
