"summary": "According to the question, A = 2 cm and Direction = + x direction v = 128 ms^{-1} $ \\therefore $ \\quad $ k = \\frac{2\\pi}{\\lambda} = \\frac{2\\pi \\times 5}{4} = 7.85 \\, \\text{rad} \\, \\text{m}^{-1} $ And \\quad $ \\mathbf{v}…",
"body": "**Key points from solved questions**\n- Given, $y = C \\sin \\left( \\frac{2\\pi}{\\lambda}(at - x) \\right)$ we can write it as $y = C \\sin \\left( \\frac{2\\pi}{\\lambda} at - \\frac{2\\pi x}{\\lambda} \\right)$ $\\omega = \\frac{2\\pi a}{\\lambda}$ The frequency $f$ is given by $f = \\frac{\\omega}{2\\pi}$ $f = \\frac{\\frac{2\\pi a}{\\lambda}}{2\\pi} = \\frac{a}{\\lambda}$ (A) According to the question, $ A = 1 \\, m $ $ \\therefore \\quad y = A \\sin(kx - \\omega t) $ $ =\\sin\\left(\\frac{2\\pi}{2\\pi}x-2\\pi\\times\\frac{1}{\\pi}t\\right) $ $ =\\sin(x-2t) $\n- It is given that, $$ \\begin{array}{l l l}{}&{y_{1}=\\textup{A}\\operatorname{s i n}\\left(\\omega t+k x+0.57\\right)\\textup{m}}&{\\dots(\\textup{i})}\\\\ {\\textup{a n d}\\quad}&{y_{2}=\\textup{A}\\operatorname{c o s}\\left(\\omega t+k x\\right)\\textup{m}}\\\\ {\\Rightarrow\\quad}&{y_{2}=\\textup{A}\\operatorname{s i n}\\left(\\frac{\\pi}{2}+\\omega t+k x\\right)\\textup{m}}&{\\dots(\\textup{i i})}\\\\ \\end{array} $$ Thus from these two equations, $ \\Delta\\phi = \\phi_{2} - \\phi_{1} $ $ =\\frac{\\pi}{2}-0.57 $ $ =1.57-0.57=1\\ rad $\n- According to the question, A = 2 cm and Direction = + x direction v = 128 ms^{-1} $ \\therefore $ \\quad $ k = \\frac{2\\pi}{\\lambda} = \\frac{2\\pi \\times 5}{4} = 7.85 \\, \\text{rad} \\, \\text{m}^{-1} $ And \\quad $ \\mathbf{v} = \\frac{\\omega}{k} = 128 \\, \\text{ms}^{-1} $ $ \\therefore $ \\quad $ \\omega = \\mathbf{v} \\times k = 128 \\times 7.85 = 1005 \\, \\text{rad} \\, \\text{s}^{-1} $ $ \\therefore $ \\quad $ y = A \\sin (kx - \\omega t) $ becomes \\quad $ y = 2 \\sin (7.85x - 1005 \\, t) $ $ = (0.02) \\sin (7.85x - 1005 \\, t) $\n- Given, $y = 0.25 \\sin (10 \\pi x - 2\\pi t)$ Comparing with equation of wave, $y = A \\sin (kx - \\omega t)$ $A = 0.25, k = 10 \\pi, \\omega = 2\\pi$ $\\frac{2\\pi}{\\lambda} = 10\\pi,$ $2\\pi f = 2\\pi$ $f = 1 \\text{ Hz}$ $\\therefore \\quad \\lambda = \\frac{1}{5} = 0.2 \\text{ m}$ When sign of coefficient of $t$ and $x$ are opposite, it means, $\\frac{dx}{dt} = v > 0$ i.e., wave is propagating in the direction of increasing $x$.\n- The general equation of wave travelling in x-direction is given as, $$ y=A\\sin\\left[\\frac{2\\pi}{\\lambda}(\\mathrm{v}t-x)\\right] $$ Here, A = 0.2 m, v = 360 ms^{-1}, $ \\lambda = 60 $ m ∴ The equation becomes, $$ y=0.2\\sin\\left[\\frac{2\\pi}{60}(360t-x)\\right] $$ $$ y=0.2\\sin\\left[2\\pi\\left(6t-\\frac{x}{60}\\right)\\right] $$",
