"body": "**Must know**\n- Series of $n$ identical cells: $\\varepsilon_{eq}=n\\varepsilon$, $r_{eq}=nr$, giving $I=\\dfrac{n\\varepsilon}{R+nr}$.\n- Parallel of $m$ identical cells: $\\varepsilon_{eq}=\\varepsilon$, $r_{eq}=\\dfrac{r}{m}$, giving $I=\\dfrac{\\varepsilon}{R+\\frac{r}{m}}$.\n- Two unequal cells in parallel: $\\varepsilon_{eq}=\\dfrac{\\varepsilon_1 r_2+\\varepsilon_2 r_1}{r_1+r_2}$ with $r_{eq}=\\dfrac{r_1 r_2}{r_1+r_2}$.\n**Exam traps**\n- Series is best when $R\\gg r$; parallel is best when $R\\ll r$.\n- Cells connected with opposing polarity have their EMFs subtract.",
