"body": "**Must know**\n- Power: $P=VI=I^2R=\\dfrac{V^2}{R}$.\n- Energy (Joule heating): $W=Pt=VIt=I^2Rt$.\n- Commercial unit of energy: $1\\ \\text{kWh}=3.6\\times10^6\\ \\text{J}$.\n- An appliance rated $(P,V)$ has resistance $R=\\dfrac{V_{rated}^2}{P_{rated}}$.\n**Exam traps**\n- Use $P=\\dfrac{V^2}{R}$ when voltage is fixed (parallel) and $P=I^2R$ when current is fixed (series).\n- In parallel the lower-resistance (higher-rated) bulb glows brighter; in series the higher-resistance bulb dissipates more.",
