"title": "How Kirchhoff's two rules solve any circuit",
"summary": "Kirchhoff's junction rule (charge conservation) and loop rule (energy conservation) provide enough independent equations to find every current in a network.",
"body": "**Must know**\n- Junction (current) rule: at any node $\\sum I_{in}=\\sum I_{out}$ — a statement of charge conservation.\n- Loop (voltage) rule: around any closed loop $\\sum \\Delta V=0$ — a statement of energy conservation.\n- Sign convention: a resistor gives $-IR$ when traversed along the current; an EMF gives $+\\varepsilon$ when traversed from $-$ to $+$.\n**Exam traps**\n- Assume current directions first; a negative result simply means the true direction is opposite.\n- Use only as many independent loop equations as there are independent loops.",
