"summary": "Given, each magnet has magnetic dipole moment = $m$.",
"body": "**Key points from solved questions**\n- Given, each magnet has magnetic dipole moment = $m$. $\\therefore$ Net magnetic moment $=\\sqrt{m^{2}+m^{2}+2m^{2}\\cos\\theta}$ Here, $m_{\\mathrm{net}}$ is max when $\\cos\\theta$ is max and $\\cos\\theta$ will be max when $\\theta$ is minimum. So, $\\theta = 30^{\\circ}, m_{\\mathrm{net}}$ will be maximum. 8.(B) The magnetic pole strength be m, then magnetic moment, $ M = ml $ From the given figure, $$ l=\\frac{\\pi}{3}\\times r $$ $$ r=\\frac{3l}{\\pi} \\tag*{...(i)}$$ ∴ New magnetic moment, $$ \\begin{aligned}\\mathbf{M}&=m\\times r=m\\times\\frac{3l}{\\pi}\\\\&=\\frac{3}{\\pi}\\times ml=\\frac{3\\mathb\n- For AC source, Given. $$ \\mathrm{V}_{\\mathrm{rms}}=12\\mathrm{~V},\\mathrm{I}_{\\mathrm{rms}}=0.2\\mathrm{~A} $$ Impedance, $$ Z=\\frac{V_{rms}}{I_{rms}}=\\frac{12}{0.2}=60\\Omega $$ and for DC source, Given. $$ V=12V,I=0.4A $$ Resistance. $$ \\mathrm{R}=\\frac{\\mathrm{V}}{\\mathrm{I}}=\\frac{12}{0.4}=30\\ \\Omega $$ Since, Z > R, we conclude there must be another component in the series, which is inductor. ∴ It is a series LR circuit.\n- From Curie Law, $ \\chi_{m} \\propto \\frac{1}{T} $",
