"body": "**Key points from solved questions**\n- A capacitor a being charged then the displacement current is $$ I=\\varepsilon\\frac{d(\\phi)}{dt} $$ $$ I=\\varepsilon_{0}\\frac{d}{dt}\\left(EA\\right) $$ $$ \\mathrm{I}=\\varepsilon_{0}\\frac{d}{dt}\\left(\\frac{\\mathrm{V}}{d}\\mathrm{A}\\right) $$ $$ \\mathrm{I}=\\frac{\\varepsilon_{0}\\mathrm{A}}{d}\\frac{d}{dt}\\left(\\frac{\\mathrm{Q}}{\\mathrm{C}}\\right) $$ $$ \\mathrm{I}=\\frac{d\\mathrm{Q}}{dt}=\\mathrm{I}_{\\text{conduction}}\\quad\\left(\\because\\mathrm{C}=\\frac{\\varepsilon_{0}\\mathrm{A}}{d}\\right) $$\n- Displacement Current, $$ I_{d}=\\frac{CdV}{dt} $$ $$ \\mathrm{I}_{d}=\\mathrm{C}\\frac{d}{dt}\\ (\\mathrm{V}_{0}\\sin\\omega t) $$ $$ I_{d}=CV_{0}\\omega\\cos\\omega t $$ $$ \\frac{\\mathrm{H}}{\\mathrm{E}}=\\sqrt{\\frac{\\varepsilon}{\\mu}} $$",
