"id": "note-ray-optics-and-optical-instruments-refraction-through-a-prism",
"chapter": "Ray Optics and Optical Instruments",
"subtopic": "Refraction through a Prism",
"class": "XII",
"unitId": "xii-optics",
"unitLabel": "Unit VII — Optics",
"order": 22,
"title": "How a prism deviates and disperses light",
"summary": "A prism bends light by a deviation angle that is least when the ray passes symmetrically; at minimum deviation n = sin[(A+δm)/2] / sin(A/2).",
"body": "**Must know**\n- Geometry: $A=r_1+r_2$ and deviation $\\delta=i_1+i_2-A$.\n- At minimum deviation (symmetric path): $n=\\dfrac{\\sin\\frac{A+\\delta_m}{2}}{\\sin\\frac{A}{2}}$.\n- Thin prism: $\\delta=(n-1)A$.\n**Exam traps**\n- The $\\delta$–$i$ graph passes through a single minimum (minimum deviation).\n- Different colours deviate by different amounts (dispersion); violet deviates most, red least.",
"formulas": [
{
"latex": "A=r_1+r_2,\\quad \\delta=i_1+i_2-A",
"meaning": "Prism geometry and deviation"
},
{
"latex": "n=\\dfrac{\\sin\\frac{A+\\delta_m}{2}}{\\sin\\frac{A}{2}}",
"meaning": "Prism formula at minimum deviation"
},
{
"latex": "\\delta=(n-1)A",
"meaning": "Deviation by a thin prism"
}
],
