"order": 24,
"title": "Why both light and matter show wave–particle duality",
"summary": "Light shows wave behaviour (interference, diffraction) and particle behaviour (the photoelectric effect); matter likewise shows both — duality is universal.",
"body": "**Must know**\n- Light: wave aspect (interference, diffraction) and particle aspect (photon, photoelectric and Compton effects).\n- Matter: particle aspect and wave aspect (de Broglie waves, electron diffraction).\n- Which aspect appears depends on the experiment performed.\n**Exam traps**\n- Wave and particle pictures are complementary, not contradictory.\n- Planck's constant $h$ is the bridge between the two descriptions.",
