"title": "reNEET2026",
"summary": "Photocurrent $\\propto$ intensity (power), so $I$ falls linearly.",
"body": "**Key points from solved questions**\n- Photocurrent $\\propto$ intensity (power), so $I$ falls linearly. Stopping potential depends only on the photon frequency, which is unchanged, so $|V|$ stays constant.\n- $\\lambda_1<\\lambda\\Rightarrow$ no emission, $V_1=0$. Stopping potential grows with threshold wavelength, and $\\lambda_3\\gg\\lambda_2$, so $V_3>V_2$, i.e. $V_2<V_3.$\n- $p_e=\\sqrt{2mE}$, $p_{ph}=E/c\\Rightarrow\\dfrac{p_e}{p_{ph}}=c\\sqrt{\\dfrac{2m}{E}}=3\\times10^8\\sqrt{\\dfrac{2(9\\times10^{-31})}{3.2\\times10^{-18}}}\\approx225.$",
