"body": "**Key points from solved questions**\n- Bohr used the concept of quantization of angular momentum. For stationary orbits, Angular momentum, $$ L=\\frac{nh}{2\\pi} $$ where, n = 1, 2, 3, ..., etc. 23.(D) $$ \\mathrm{E}=\\frac{h c}{\\lambda}\\Rightarrow\\lambda=\\frac{h c}{\\mathrm{E}}\\Rightarrow\\lambda\\propto\\frac{1}{\\mathrm{E}} $$ Energy of photon of wavelength $ \\lambda_{1} $ $$ \\Delta\\mathrm{E}_{1}=-\\left(\\frac{5\\mathrm{E}}{2}\\right)+4\\mathrm{E}=\\frac{3\\mathrm{E}}{2} $$ Energy of photon of wavelength $ \\lambda_{2} $, $$ \\Delta\\mathrm{E}_{2}=-2\\mathrm{E}-(-3\\mathrm{E}) $$ $$ \\Delta\\mathrm{E}_{2}=-2\\mathrm{E}+3\\mathrm{E}=",
