"order": 27,
"title": "How semiconductor devices build up from bands and junctions",
"summary": "Semiconductor electronics builds from band theory → intrinsic/extrinsic semiconductors → the p-n junction → the diode and its rectifier applications.",
"body": "**Must know**\n- The band gap classifies solids; doping tunes conductivity into n-type or p-type.\n- A p-n junction forms a depletion region and barrier → the diode conducts one way → rectifiers convert AC to DC.\n- Silicon ($E_g\\approx1.1\\ \\text{eV}$) and germanium ($\\approx0.7\\ \\text{eV}$) are the workhorse materials.\n**Exam traps**\n- Semiconductors have a negative temperature coefficient of resistance.\n- A diode conducts in forward bias; a rectifier converts AC → DC.",
